<HEAD>`Cocktail' Mixes It Up At Box Office</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RICHARD DE ATLEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``Cocktail,'' starring Tom Cruise as an
acrobatic bartender who gets shaken and stirred by romance, was
moviegoers' choice last weekend as it earned $11.7 million at the
nation's box offices.
   Besides ``Cocktail,'' Walt Disney had two other films in the top
10 _ ``Who Framed Roger Rabbit'' and ``Bambi.''
   ``Roger Rabbit'' came in second with $6.5 million in ticket
sales, followed by the Eddie Murphy comedy ``Coming To America,''
which earned $6.4 million for third place.
   ``Die Hard,'' starring Bruce Willis as an off-duty cop caught in
a terrorist take-over of a high-rise building, was in fourth place
with $6.1 million, followed by the Robert DeNiro-Charles Grodin
comedy adventure ``Midnight Run,'' which earned $4.6 million.
   ``The Dead Pool'' shot down $3.5 million for sixth place, while
``Bambi'' earned $3.2 million for seventh.
   Rounding out the top 10 list was ``Big,'' with $3.1 million for
eighth place, followed by ``Caddyshack II'' with $2.3 million and
``Big Top Pee-wee,'' which earned $2.2 million.
   John Cleese's ``A Fish Called Wanda,'' about intrigue, romance
and class comparisons in London, managed an 11th place spot even
though it showed on only 192 screens. The movie earned $2 million
for a $10,438 per screen average.
   Making their debuts this week are Columbia Pictures ``Vibes,''
Warner Bros. ``Clean and Sober,'' and Touchstone's ``The Rescue.''
   Here are the top films for the weekend as tallied by Exhibitor
Relations, with distributor, weekend gross, number of theater
screens, average per screen, total gross, number of weeks in
release and estimated production costs when available.
   1. ``Cocktail,'' Disney, $11.7 million, 1,404 screens, $8,397
per screen, $11.7 million, one week, n-a.
   2. ``Who Framed Roger Rabbit,'' Disney, $6.5 million, 1,429
screens, $4,588 per screen, $95.3 million, six weeks, $40 million.
   3. ``Coming To America,'' Paramount, $6.4 million, 1,902
screens, $3,381 per screen, $92 million, five weeks, $20 million.
   4. ``Die Hard,'' 20th Century Fox, $6.1 million, 1,324 screens,
$4,613 per screen, $20.1 million, three weeks, $24 million.
   5. ``Midnight Run,'' Universal, $4.6 million, 1,161 screens,
$4,005 per screen, $14.7 million, two weeks, $20 million.
   6. ``The Dead Pool,'' Warner Bros., $3.5 million, 1,651 screens,
$2,172 per screen, $29.2 million, three weeks, $18 million.
   7. ``Bambi,'' Disney, $3.2 million, 1,477 screens, $2,168 per
screen, $24.9 million, three weeks, $2 million (in 1942).
   8. ``Big,'' 20th Century Fox, $3.1 million, 1,254 screens,
$2,506 per screen, $80.4 million, nine weeks, $15 million.
   9. ``Caddyshack II,'' Warner Bros., $2.3 million, 1,556 screens,
$1,508 per screen, $8.9 million, two weeks, $15 million.
   10. ``Big Top Pee-wee,'' Paramount, $2.2 million, 1,256 screens,
$1,776 per screen, $9.2 million, two weeks, $18 million.
