<HEAD>71-year-old Man Swims Around Manhattan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 71-year-old man who swam around Manhattan now
plans to swim across the English Channel and around Catalina Island
off California in memory of a son he lost in an automobile accident.
   ``Every time I swim, it's a tribute to Richard,'' Ashby Harper
said. Harper has dedicated all his marathon swimming efforts to his
son since 1981, the year he died.
   ``I'm doing something that has ruined men half my age,'' said
the prep school headmaster from Albuquerque, N.M., of the three
swims before completing Sunday's 28.5-mile trip around Manhattan in
8 hours 34 minutes.
   He said the Channel swim on Aug. 21 and the excursion around
Catalina Island on Sept. 12 will be more difficult.
   Harper became the oldest person to cross the 21-mile Channel in
1983. He had held the record for the oldest person to swim around
Manhattan until his record was broken in 1984 by 73-year-old Adrian
Kanaar.
</TEXT>
