non-disclosure pledges signed by government workers with access to
secret information must sign to retain their security clearances.
   In the order signed Friday and made public Monday, the judge
said the government must provide a more specific definition of the
term ``classifiable information.''
   In signing the various pledges, government employees promise not
to make unauthorized disclosures of top-secret information or
``classifiable information.''
