<HEAD>Firefighters' Union Endorses Dukakis</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Delegates to the annual convention of
the International Association of Fire Fighters voted overwhelmingly
to endorse Democrat Michael Dukakis in this year's presidential
election.
   The 1,200 delegates to the 170,000-member union passed a
resolution Monday saying the Massachusetts governor had done more
for firefighters than the Reagan administration, spokesman Henry
Fleischer said.
   The resolution said ``firefighters cannot be burdened for
another four years with a president who is indifferent to the needs
and concerns of firefighters,'' Fleischer said.
   The IAFF statement said that as governor of Massachusetts,
Dukakis has shown that he ``understands firefighters' issues and
has demonstrated his support in Massachusetts by signing into law
several petitions that benefit fire fighters and their families.''
