<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Police Car,0187</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Unmarked Police Car Found In Drug Raid</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN LEANDRO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An unmarked police car, complete with
moveable spotlight, antennas and police scanner, was discovered
during a drug raid, police said.
   The 1984 car, which probably had been auctioned off, may have
been used to deliver illegal drugs, Lt. Tom Hull said on Monday.
   ``That's our impression,'' Hull said. ``You see it going down
the road, who's going to stop it?''
   Officers arrested John Gilbert Nunes, 41, and DeAnn Marie Stone,
20, on Friday, he said. They also seized $9,000, a submachine gun
and nearly a dozen other weapons, as well as seven pounds of
methamphetamine and a half-pound of cocaine, Hull said. Police put
the value of the drugs at $300,000.
   Investigators said they are not sure what police agency once
owned the car.
   ``We auction them off,'' Hull said. ``It could be anybody's.''
   Stone was booked for investigation of methamphetamine for sale.
Nunes faces a half-dozen additional charges, including possession
of a machine gun, possession of an explosive device and possession
of a sawed-off shotgun.
