<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--All-Elvis Station,0126</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Radio Station Adopts All-Presley Format</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A radio station has adopted a new format of
Elvis Presley songs and trivia 24 hours a day.
   WCVG-AM began the format at noon Monday. The station's general
manager, John Stolz, said there is plenty of recorded material to
supply the station's needs.
   ``Elvis recorded 659 singles and 90 albums,'' Stolz said. ``I
don't think any other artist today can live up to that stature.
Most radio stations today work from a playlist of 400 to 500 songs.
We'll have at least 659.''
   Presley died Aug. 16, 1977, at his Graceland mansion home in
Memphis, Tenn., of a reported heart attack.
   The station previously played country music and then top-40.
