<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--CashFound     08-02 0159</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Cash Found,0164</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Claims A $17,600 Stack of Cash Found Along A Road</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WINNETKA, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man has claimed $17,600 that was found
last week along a parkway, police said.
   A woman found the bundle of $100 bills Thursday while walking
and turned it over to police, police Lt. Joseph Sumner said.
   ``The gentleman is very lucky, and the finder is very honest,''
Sumner said.
   Sumner refused to release the name of the man or the woman.
   The man lost the money Wednesday night and searched for it all
day Thursday, the lieutenant said. Then he heard a news report that
a bundle of money had been found, and he went to police to claim
it, Sumner said.
   Sumner said the man correctly identified the exact amount, its
denominations and that the cash was bound with a rubber band.
   Police also verified that the man had received $17,600 in cash
for business services, Sumner said.
</TEXT>
