<2ND_LINE>PM-Germany-Spy Appeal,0189</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>U.S. Military Appeals For Information On Spy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DARMSTADT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. Armed Forces newspaper
today appealed to servicemen and their families to come forward
with information about a man suspected of being an East German spy.
   Investigators at the Bitburg Air Base, 13 miles from the
Luxembourg border, asked that the article appear in the Stars and
Stripes newspaper, said Larine Barr, a spokeswoman for the U.S. Air
Force Office of Special Investigations.
   Ms. Barr said investigators believe the man, known as
``Mickei,'' no longer lives in the area and has fled to East
Germany.
   According to the brief article on the second page of Stars and
Stripes, Mickei worked as a taxi driver in the Bitburg area and
owned a camping trailer. ``The man often held weekend parties at
his trailer,'' Stars and Stripes said. It printed a telephone
number for people to call if they had any information.
   It said investigators are ``exploring the possibility that Air
Force members or members of their families had contact with the man
or have details about him.''
</TEXT>
