<HEAD>Audience Jeers Kirov Ballet Delay</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The audience at an opening performance by the
Kirov ballet booed and hissed because the show was delayed for an
hour by workers still installing seats in the temporary theater.
   The final checks of the house ``ran a bit longer than
expected,'' said Zoe Coles, spokeswoman at the Business Design
Center in north London.
   She said the center had installed 3,200 seats in six days,
transforming the exhibition and conference center into a theater
the size of the Kirov's Mariinsky theater in Leningrad.
   The week-long appearance by the Kirov performing ``Giselle'' at
the Business Design Center is the second of the Kirov's
three-theater London tour.
   Last week the company performed ``Giselle'' at the London
Coliseum, home of the English National Opera, and next week will
dance ``Le Corsaire'' at Covent Garden.
   Ms. Coles said that using the Business Design Center meant more
people could come because of cheaper tickets. Tickets to the
Business Design Center performance cost from $14.50 to $60,
compared with $76 to $119 at Covent Garden.
