<HEAD>Salvadoran President Begins Second Round of Cancer Treatments</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Salvadorean President Jose Napoleon Duarte was
reported ``in excellent spirits'' Tuesday at Walter Reed Army
Medical Center as he began a second round of treatments for
terminal liver cancer.
   ``His condition will be re-evaluated and he is expected to be
hospitalized for about 10 days,'' said a hospital statement.
