<HEAD>1.3 Million Students Win Academic Fitness Awards</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 1.3 million students earned
Presidential Academic Fitness Awards this year, the Department of
Education said Tuesday.
   The winners finished elementary, junior high or high school with
grade averages of B-plus or better and achievement test scores in
the top 20 percent on standardized tests.
   The program rules also allow principals to present awards to a
limited number of students who demonstrated extraordinary effort
but did not meet all the criteria.
   Each of the 1,315,081 winners, from 47,166 public and private
schools, are receiving a certificate signed by President Reagan,
Secretary of Education William J. Bennett and the school principal.
   The recognition program, in its fifth year, is modeled after the
presidential physical fitness awards.
</TEXT>
