<1ST_LINE>r w AM-DishwasherRepair     08-02 0158</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Dishwasher Repair,150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Safety Agency Issues Dishwasher Warning</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Modifications are needed on five types of
Whirlpool undercounter dishwashers that could catch fire, the
Consumer Product Safety Commission warned Tuesday.
   Whirlpool Corp. of Benton Harbor, Mich., is offering to replace
the potentially faulty selector switch on the approximately 75,000
dishwashers, the commission reported.
   Involved are Whirlpool undercounter dishwasher models
DU7400XS-0, DU7600XS-0, DU7800XS-0, DU900XR-0 and DU900XR-1.
   According to the company, the pushbutton selector switch, under
certain circumstances, could catch fire. Twelve incidents have been
reported, the safety agency said.
   Whirlpool is asking owners of the washers to telephone the
company at 1-800-541-5746 to arrange for the free repairs.
Consumers can check the model number on a plate found on the right
front edge of the tub after the door is opened.
   Safety officials urged owners not to use the washers until the
repairs are completed.
   Consumers needing more information can contact the safety
commission at 1-800-638-2772.
</TEXT>
