<HEAD>13 Die In Bus Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN LUIS POTOSI, Mexico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thirteen people died and 18 were
injured when a passenger bus slammed into a truck that has just
overturned on a highway early Tuesday, Federal Highway Police said.
   Ricardo Rijoas, a highway police spokesman, said 11 people died
at the scene and two more died in a hospital in San Luis Potosi,
capital of the north central state of the same name. The dead
included the bus driver, Riojas said.
   The accident took place on the San Luis Potosi-Queretaro highway
37 miles south of San Luis Potosi. The city is 334 miles north of
Mexico City.
   Highway police said the speeding trailer truck had overturned
only moments before the Omnibus del Jorullo bus came down the
highway. They said the truck driver abandoned his rig and has not
been found.
   The impact threw the bus against an embankment, they said.
