<DOCNO> AP880802-0256 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-08-02-88 0735EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>u f PM-Japan-Markets     08-02 0176</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Japan-Markets,0186</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Tokyo Stock Prices Rise While Dollar Drops</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices closed higher while the dollar
declined today in slow trading in Tokyo.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, which gained 126.37 points Monday, rose 40.02
points, or 0.14 percent, closing at 28,366.33.
   After opening lower, share prices rebounded on late buying
concentrated in heavy electrical and construction issues, dealers
said.
   The blue chip stocks and large-capital steel and heavy
industrial issues, which have led the market for some months,
faltered and left the market adrift in the morning session, they
added.
   Advancing issues outnumbered decliners, 448 to 418, with 179
others unchanged.
   On the Tokyo Foreign Exchange, the dollar opened at 132.65 yen
and ranged between 132.30 yen and 132.70 yen before closing at
132.40 yen, down 0.85 yen from Monday's close.
   Foreign exchange dealers said market participants did not expect
much market-moving news until Friday, when U.S. employment figures
are to be released.
   Spot trading totaled $4.253 billion, up from Monday's $3.664
billion.
</TEXT>
