<HEAD>London Stocks Lower At Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices drifted lower Tuesday amid a lack of
trading interest with many players away on summer vacations.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange index of 100 selected issues
was down 8.1 points, or 0.4 percent, at 1,854.1 at midday.
   Overall volume was moderate at 224.4 million shares compared
with 218.8 million shares at the same time Monday.
   There was little news to affect stock prices, and even takeover
speculation that has bolstered selected stocks in recent sessions
dried up.
   Dealers said they were not surprised that prices moved lower,
after four consecutive gains took the FT-SE index toward the top
end of its recent trading range.
   Stocks also drifted lower in line with selling on the futures
markets, some dealers said.
