approval to an agreement with the United States covering imports of
a dozen farm products, officials said.
   The expected action liberalizes import restrictions on eight out
of 12 agricultural items designated by the General Agreement on
Tariffs and Trade such as non-citrus fruit juices. These items were
the subject of diplomatic acrimony between the two nations against
the backdrop of a larger trade confrontation over access to Japan's
beef market earlier this year.
