<2ND_LINE>PM-Earns-Sun,0205</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Sun Microsystems Breaks Billion-Dollar Mark</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sun Microsystems Inc.'s profit more
than doubled in its fiscal fourth quarter as its full-year revenue
passed the billion-dollar mark, the company sais.
   Sun reached $1 billion in annual revenue in six years, getting
to the mark about a year sooner than Apple Computer Inc. did and
coming close to the five-year record of Houston-based Compaq
Computer Corp.
   The company reported fourth-quarter net income that more than
doubled to $25.3 million or 66 cents a share from $10.9 million or
31 cents a share in the year earlier period.
   Revenues increased 96 percent to $365.1 million from $185.9
million.
   For the year, net income was up 83 percent to $66.4 million, or
$1.79 a share, from $36.3 million, or $1.11 a share. Revenue rose
to $1.05 billion from $537.5 million, a 96 percent increase.
   Scott McNealy, the president and chief executive, warned that
sales increases in the first quarter are likely to be only modest
when compared with the period that ended in June.
   He said the company made a big effort to increase shipments and
reduce its backlog in the fourth quarter.
</TEXT>
