<TEXT>
   Dow Chemical Co. will purchase 10 million
of its 190 million outstanding shares of stock, the company said
today.
   Dow has bought more than 20 million shares through nine
repurchase programs since August 1983. The most recent was in May.
   Enrique C. Falla, financial vice president of Dow, said because
it is currently undervalued and because Dow predicts continuing
