<HEAD>Stocks Off</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Updates thruout with closing comment and prices.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices fell Tuesday on the London Stock
Exchange in a lackluster session.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index fell 6.7
points, or 0.4 percent, to 1,855.5.
   Volume was a moderate 376.5 million shares, down from 381.7
million shares a day earlier.
   Stock prices remained locked in a narrow range throughout the
day, dealers said. The other major markets failed to provide much
impetus to London stocks.
   The majority of British blue chip stocks closed lower as the low
trading volume prompted market makers to push down prices in an
effort to generate some buying interest. A handful of shares bucked
the negative trend on dividend-related buying or special situations.
   The Financial Times 30-share index fell 5.1 points to 1,491.4.
The Financial Times 500-share index fell 3.1 points to close at
1,058.5.
