<2ND_LINE>AM-Steel Mill,0167</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>West German Firm Buys 80-Year-Old Steel Mill</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EAST PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A West German firm has agreed to
buy and modernize an 80-year-old steel mill here, possibly tripling
employment at the plant, officials announced Tuesday.
   Korf KG has agreed to buy the mill from Rhode Island Forging
Steel Inc. and make it a supplier for the Connecticut Steel Corp.'s
Wallingford, Conn., facility. Terms of the deal were not disclosed
and some Connecticut Steel shareholders were said to be involved in
the purchase.
   The mill currently employs 50 people, but that number could
triple within the next two years, Louis A. Fazzano, director of the
state Department of Economic Development, said in a news release.
   The plant currently melts down scrap steel, forming it into
semi-finished billets that are sold to rolling mills around the
world. It will become the prime supplier of billets to Connecticut
Steel's rolling mill and wire drawing plant in Wallingford, the
release said.
</TEXT>
