<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-WesternUnion     08-02 0198</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Western Union,0206</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Western Union Loses $3 Million During Second Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>UPPER SADDLE RIVER, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Western Union Corp. posted a
$2.99 million loss during its second quarter, the company announced
Tuesday.
   The latest loss compared to a loss of $990,000 during the same
period in 1987.
   Revenue during the quarter rose to $235 million from $206.5
million.
   The telecommunications company lost $628.2 million during the
first six months of 1988, compared with a $19.8 million loss in the
first half of 1987, due largely to restructuring charges of $603
million in the first quarter, resulting from Western Union's recent
reorganization.
   Revenue during the six-month period rose to $469.5 million from
$411.1 million in the same period a year ago.
   Year-earlier figures do not include revenue from the former ITT
World Communications Inc., which Western Union acquired Dec. 30.
Including income from the business, now known as Worldcom, revenue
would have been $266 million in second quarter 1987 and $522
million in the first half of last year.
   Following a series of unprofitable years, Western Union
completed a plan Dec. 30 to reorganize and move from providing
communications facilities to providing specialized business and
consumer services.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
